<p>Long-term international migration counts moves intended to last <strong>12 months or
more</strong>. It does not count visitors, short courses, or seasonal work under a year. In
the year ending March 2026 the Home Office granted over 2.2 million visitor visas, and not
one of them appears in the figures on this page.</p>

<h2>Net migration over time</h2>

<p>Net migration is immigration minus emigration. It is not a count of arrivals, and nobody
is "a net migrant" — see <a href="/common-claims/net-migration-is-arrivals/">the claim
check</a>.</p>

