<h2>Why people came</h2>

<p>ONS publishes a breakdown by reason for <strong>non-EU+ arrivals only</strong>, which were
627,000 of the {% figure "migration/total-long-term-immigration" %} total. There is no equivalent
breakdown of net migration by reason, and constructing one by subtracting emigration from a
category would not be valid.</p>

